<TITLE> Congress outlines bailout bill </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Washington, Sep 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US congressional leaders on Sunday said they had reached the broad outline of a deal to put in place a $700 billion bank bailout but were awaiting details on paper before declaring it final. "We've made great progress," House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi told reporters after a night of marathon talks. "We have to get it committed to paper so we can formally agree."
